\begin{definition*}[Isomorphism]
  {}
  Let~\CatC be a category, let~$\Obja,\Objb \in \CatC$ be objects, and let~$\mora \colon \Obja \mto \Objb$ be a morphism. We say that~$\mora$ is an \emph{\iindex{isomorphism}} if there exists a morphism~$\morb\colon \Objb \to \Obja$ such that~$\mora \mthen \morb = \catid_{\Obja}$ and~$\morb \mthen \mora = \catid_{\Objb}$.\end{definition*}
